    base:desc "The framework supports four main lifecycle stages: (1) **Device Modeling** – Building Control Engineers enrich BIM models with explicit sensor, actuator, and controller descriptions (Definition of BCS components) to overcome BIM’s static representation limitation; (2) **Model Transformation** – Applying Model‑Driven Engineering (MDE) principles, the enriched BIM is automatically parsed into a structured, deployable Digital Twin artifact, managing the transition from static architectural representation to a dynamic runtime model; (3) **Deployment & Runtime Operation** – The generated DT is deployed to the edge or cloud, with real‑time data exchange protocols maintaining continuous synchronization with the physical building; Facility Managers then monitor and interact with the twin via interactive visualization interfaces; (4) **Service Extension & Governance** – A modular architecture with standardized extension points allows DT Engineers to integrate custom analytics or control plugins, enabling governance of evolution and reduced manual configuration during any lifecycle transition."
